bbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11979.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/genchi_x/Hige2.txt height=123 width=130></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bowling for Columbine</span><hr size=1> I saw it long ago when it was first realeased <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Very very good movie. Also has a kool interview with Marilyn Manson as well s a not-so-kool one with Charlton Heston. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
Click to wander the halls of the delicious  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://omu.kuiki.net/bbs" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;">OMU</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=terminalspiritdisease@polykarbonbbs>Terminal Spirit Disease</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/7/03 12:53:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11979.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> !</span><hr size=1> Ha ha ha, wait, you honest to god thought you were digesting facts? That's why I prefer to stay away from Moore &quot;documentaries&quot;...whereas documentaries are supposed to be objective and let you decide your stance on an issue, Moore is pretty contempt with skewing the facts and making your mind up for you. <br>
<br>
And of course, when the well runs dry of facts to distort, in comes the acclaimed &quot;comedy&quot;...which is merely &quot;gun owners are dumb hicks har har har har,&quot; which I might find amusing, if it weren't substituting and trying to pose as a fact to make up the viewer's mind.<br>
<br>
And really, I don't get how Moore stumbled upon some amazing facts by interviewing Heston...the dude's got Alzheimer's disease, of course he might say something stupid, he's got a brain disorder! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=amonitaverosa>amonita verosa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/7/03 4:29:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11979.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bowling for Columbine</span><hr size=1> TSD- I said <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>some</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> facts. the numbers for gun realted deaths I thought was pretty interesting...I might be off, but I believe in canada (which was pretty high compared to most other countries)was at 160 something; while the states was at 11,700 something. even taking population ratios into account (which moore didn't mention, but he was also trying to make a point)that's pretty damn high.<br>
and I kinda take offence to the umm.... digesting facts comment. personally, this documentry compliments the beliefs I've had on the subject for many years. I thought it was nice to hear someone else say it...but I guess I'm biased too.<br>
I do agree that the documentry was a little biased in its opinions, but when I went to go see it, it was being presented as more of a film.<br>
I do think the interviews were kind of pointless between hefner and clarke,but at the same time, hefner could have been a little more empathetic at the nra conventions he held right after the columbine massacur and in littleton. I don't agree with moore that the dates should have been cancelled and that hefner is a huge monster because of it since all those cons would have been prebooked. Also though, one of the points he brings up during the film is to watch the media objectivly. so please don't assume that becuase I've seen and liked this film, that I will automatically be catorgurizing myself as someone that will swallow anything.<br>
thanks<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/amonita_verosa/void.htm">www.geocities.com/amonita...a/void.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=terminalspiritdisease@polykarbonbbs>Terminal Spirit Disease</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/7/03 5:20:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11979.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> !</span><hr size=1> Actually, the comment was more out of surprise, and even then, I really over exaggerated that surprise (because obviously there are going to be some facts)...my apologies if that sounded condescending. <br>
<br>
Among other factors, I had seen Roger &amp; Me before Bowling for Columbine, so I was completely sure when I went to go see the movie that Moore would lie his arse off to drive his point home...and so keeping that premise in mind, it's kind of surprising when I hear people pretty much agreeing with every point the film brought up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yeef>Yeef</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/7/03 6:09:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11979.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/genchi_x/Hige2.txt height=123 width=130></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: !</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>which is merely &quot;gun owners are dumb hicks har har har har,&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I don't remember him saying anything like that at all. I know that Michael Moore happens to a registered member of the NRA. I felt that the major point of the film was that the American media produces a culture of fear. That's probably why he included the stuff about how many guns there are in Canada adn about the way news is handled over there. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
