<br>
Well, he did interview Charleston freaking Heston--I don't see what other point he was trying to make interviewing him other than to ridicule gun owners via a generalization (&quot;their leader is a nut, therefore...&quot;). And then there were the animations...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I know that Michael Moore happens to a registered member of the NRA.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The way I see it, that's the central part of the ploy (and happened to piss me off the most)--by saying that, he thinks he can come across as being unbiased here, and I'm not fooled at all by that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dynamiteneon>DynamiteNeon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>TBA</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/7/03 9:54:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11979.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mangaden.com/pics/junk/b.jpg width=75 length=75></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: !</span><hr size=1> I don't agree.  In fact, I'm not even sure that bowling for columbine was completely about being anti-gun.  He seemed to have more of an interest in why AMERICANS specifically have so many problems with guns as opposed to some other countries.<br>
<br>
Or, he may be anti gun, as he was showing scenes like the one about getting guns and bullets away from Kmart, but I still walked away thinking more about why America seems to have such a violent gun culture in relation to the rest of the world.<br>
<br>
And regardless of his pro/anti gun stance, I still think there were some really good points made about how the media in general likes to promote fear in people either to get ratings or to keep us all as little, mindless consumers.  It's a hard thing to argue when you look at the differences of our news programs compared to some other countries like canada or elsewhere.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=11979.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=11979.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11979.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=11979.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.threadControl?topicID=11979.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11979.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11979.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub25.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpa